result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony Gallegos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:39 AM Defendant Anthony Gallegos in court.  Attorney KRISTIAN V NORDBY in court for Anthony Gallegos.  Prosecuting attorney Brian Van Schyndel in court for the State of Wisconsin. CASE RECALLED AT 11:40AM:  Defendant Anthony Gallegos in court.  Attorney KRISTIAN V NORDBY in court for Anthony Gallegos.  Prosecuting attorney Jessica Lynott in court for the State of Wisconsin. Digital Court Reporter: Hannah Wronkowski.  The court sentenced the defendant unknowing he lived in Illinois and the State of Wisconsin will not monitor the defendant on misd. charges while living in the State of Illinois.  The State notes this offer was amended by another ADA and then transferred back to ADA Lynott.  The State is willing to offer 1 day CFTS and fines on all the charges or the deft. would need to move to Wisconsin to be monitored.  Defendant will accept the fines.
